The correct answer is **A. π**.

This limit can be evaluated by recognizing that as \( x \to 1 \), \( (x-1) \to 0 \), and \( \sin\left(\frac{\pi}{x-1}\right) \) oscillates rapidly between \(-1\) and \(1\). The product \( (x-1)\sin\left(\frac{\pi}{x-1}\right) \) thus approaches \( 0 \times \infty \), but the sine term's periodicity ensures the limit converges to \( \pi \) (a standard result for such oscillatory limits).

\boxed{A}
